# Architecture

## External standards

Company or team standards that apply to this project. Agents read these as hard constraints — same weight as architectural decisions.

- **Approved tech stack:** <e.g., "Backend: Python only — company standard. Frontend: React or vanilla JS.">
- **Forbidden without approval:** <e.g., "No new databases without architecture review. No GPL dependencies.">
- **Codestyle guide:** <link or inline key rules — e.g., "https://company.internal/codestyle/python">
- **Required tooling:** <e.g., "pylint + mypy + black. CI must pass before merge.">

If no company standards apply — remove this section.

